Download Putty and install it on your PC
Get the IP address of the Raspberry PI
Make sure the port number is set at 22

******************************************
Input the IP address of the Raspberry Pi and click next
Default login name and password is (pi and raspberry)
If connection is successful, Great you are in the Raspberry Pi wirelessly

*****************************************
Run the following basic python codes  in the Putty to update the Raspberry Pi

sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get upgrade
